      <p class="section-desc">
        Every choice here was deliberate. These are the architectural decisions that shaped the lab,
        written as comments in a config file because that felt right.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-cmd">
      <span class="prompt-dollar">$</span> cat /etc/homelab/decisions.conf
    </div>
    <div class="terminal homelab-animate">
      <div class="terminal__bar">
        <span class="terminal__dot terminal__dot--red"></span>
        <span class="terminal__dot terminal__dot--yellow"></span>
        <span class="terminal__dot terminal__dot--green"></span>
        <span class="terminal__bar-title">decisions.conf</span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal__content">
        <pre class="config-file"><span class="config-comment"># /etc/homelab/decisions.conf</span>
<span class="config-comment"># Last updated: Mar 2026</span>
<span class="config-sep"># ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────</span>

<span class="config-key"># WHY: Cloudflare Tunnels over Port Forwarding</span>
<span class="config-val">Zero open ports on the router. Outbound-only HTTPS</span>
<span class="config-val">connections. Free TLS, DDoS protection, and WAF.</span>
<span class="config-val">No need to touch router settings or expose home IP.</span>

<span class="config-key"># WHY: External SSD for Immich Storage</span>
<span class="config-val">Data lives independently of the host machine.</span>
<span class="config-val">Portable and upgradeable. Auto-mounts via fstab UUID.</span>
<span class="config-val">The MacBook could be replaced without losing a single photo.</span>

<span class="config-key"># WHY: Distributed ML Processing</span>
<span class="config-val">Heavy ML tasks (face detection, smart search) offloaded</span>
<span class="config-val">to a Windows laptop with NVIDIA GPU over LAN.</span>
<span class="config-val">Main server stays lean. Both nodes update independently.</span>
<span class="config-val">If GPU node goes down, Immich queues jobs gracefully.</span>

<span class="config-key"># WHY: Headless MacBook as Server</span>
<span class="config-val">Custom lid-monitor systemd service turns off display</span>
<span class="config-val">when lid closes without suspending. Sleep/hibernate</span>
<span class="config-val">disabled entirely. 24/7 uptime with minimal power draw.</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

